Uses of Component in com.constantcontact.components.common.tracking
 

Subclasses of Component in com.constantcontact.components.common.tracking
 class TrackingBase
          Base class for all the Email Campaign Tracking classes used by the Email Campaign Tracking Service in Constant Contact.
Base class for all the Contact Tracking classes used by the Contact Tracking Service in Constant Contact.
It defines the common fields: Contact Id Activity Type Campaign Id Email Address Each sub-class will come with a particular value for Activity Type, depending on the answer type.
Each sub-class will also add its own new fields, depending on the business logic.

 class ContactList
          Represents a Contacts List for the Contact Service in Constant Contact.
It may contain from one to many contacts.
Doesn't actually store any contacts! BUT each Contact has an internal reference to the list(s) it is a member of.
That "list of lists" can be retrieved using Contact.getLists()

Subclasses of Component in com.constantcontact.components.emailcampaigns
 class EmailCampaignBase
          Represents a single Email Campaign Base for the Email Campaign Service in Constant Contact.
Response and Request classes extend this.
 class EmailCampaignRequest
          Represents a single Email Campaign Request for the Email Campaign Service in Constant Contact.
Always use this class when creating a request, and not the base one!
The private inner fields are just the same as in EmailCampaignBase, but JSON annotations are different for the overwritten, hiding fields forbidden by the server.
 class EmailCampaignResponse
          Represents a single Email Campaign Response for the Email Campaign Service in Constant Contact.
 class MessageFooter
          Represents a single Message Footer from an EmailCampaignBase for the Email Campaign Service in Constant Contact.
 class SentToContactList
          Represents a single Sent to Contact List from EmailCampaignBase for the Email Campaign Service in Constant Contact.
 class TrackingSummary
          Represents a single Tracking Summary from EmailCampaignBase for the Email Campaign Service in Constant Contact.
This is expected in a response and should never be sent in a request - since this contains statistical data generated by the server.
It is actually hidden in EmailCampaignRequest.
